# Responsive Design Rules

## Core Principles
- ALWAYS use mobile-first design
- Build layouts for small screens first, then scale up
- Prioritize usability over visual complexity

## Layout
- Use Flexbox or CSS Grid, NEVER fixed positioning unless necessary
- Avoid fixed widths (px). Prefer %, rem, vw
- Stack elements vertically on small screens
- Use max-width instead of fixed width

## Breakpoints
- Use minimal breakpoints:
  - sm: 640px
  - md: 768px
  - lg: 1024px
- Let content determine breakpoints, not devices

## Typography
- Minimum font-size: 16px
- Ensure readable line-height (1.4–1.6)
- Avoid long text blocks on mobile

## Touch & Interaction
- Minimum tap target: 44x44px
- Add spacing between clickable elements
- Avoid hover-only interactions

## Images & Media
- Use responsive images:
  - max-width: 100%
  - height: auto
- Lazy load images when possible

## Performance
- Minimize large images and heavy animations
- Prefer simple transitions over complex effects

## Navigation
- Use simple navigation (hamburger or bottom nav)
- Limit number of visible options

## What NOT To Do
- Do NOT use fixed pixel layouts
- Do NOT cram desktop layout into mobile
- Do NOT rely on hover effects
- Do NOT create horizontal scrolling layouts

## Tailwind Guidelines
- Mobile styles first, then scale:
  - text-sm md:text-lg
- Use responsive utilities instead of custom media queries
